{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"sisterly-dynastical-ocelot","description":"Add a `make worktree name=<branch>` target that creates a fresh git worktree\nbranched from current `origin/main` and fully provisions its local env in one\nstep — so agents and humans stop hand-running the multi-command worktree setup\nthe repo's CLAUDE.md / docs/local-dev-env.md prescribe.\n\n## Why\nThe repo mandates working in a fresh worktree branched from `origin/main` with its\nown local venv (never the main checkout, never a stale global build). Today that is\na documented but manual sequence (`git fetch` → `git worktree add` → create venv →\n`make install`), which is error-prone and easy to shortcut. A single target makes\nthe canonical setup one command, matches the repo's existing Makefile idiom, and\nneeds no new per-developer dependency (git + python + the existing `make install`).\nThis is the wrapper-command approach chosen over direnv: it matches \"provision on\ncreation\" semantics, works identically for humans, agents, and non-interactive CI,\nand reuses the ONE canonical `make install` path rather than forking it.\n\n## What\nAdd a `worktree` target to `Makefile` that:\n- Requires a `name=<branch>` argument; prints usage and exits non-zero if absent.\n- Creates the worktree at `../<name>` (overridable via `dir=<path>`), branched from\n  freshly-fetched `origin/main` (`git fetch origin` then\n  `git worktree add <dir> -b <name> origin/main`).\n- Provisions the venv via the SAME sequence the docs bless and this change dogfoods:\n  `python3 -m venv .venv` (seeds pip so the canonical installer works) then, with the\n  venv active, `$(MAKE) install` (editable `.[dev]` install + `make hooks` wiring the\n  pre-commit gate). No bespoke pip line — it delegates to the existing canonical path.\n- Prints a final \"activate with: cd <dir> && source .venv/bin/activate\" hint.\n- Is added to `.PHONY` and carries a `## ` help string so `make help` lists it.\n\nThe Gerrit `commit-msg` hook is inherited automatically (worktrees share the common\ngit dir's hooks), so the target does not re-fetch it — a note in the recipe records\nwhy. Register the new target's purpose with a one-line mention in\n`docs/local-dev-env.md` so it is discoverable next to the manual sequence it replaces.\n\n## Scope\n- `Makefile`: new `worktree` target + `.PHONY` entry.\n- `docs/local-dev-env.md`: one line pointing at `make worktree name=<branch>` as the\n  one-command form of the documented manual setup.\n- Non-goal: direnv / auto-activation on `cd` (a different concern — ongoing activation,\n  not creation-time provisioning); non-goal: a `post-checkout` hook; non-goal: removing\n  the manual instructions (kept as the explanation of what the target automates).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `make worktree` with NO `name=` prints a usage message and exits non-zero.\n      Proving command: `make worktree 2>&1; test $? -ne 0 && echo USAGE-OK`\n- [ ] `make worktree name=<tmp>` creates a worktree at `../<tmp>` on a new branch\n      `<tmp>` whose HEAD equals current `origin/main`, containing a populated `.venv`\n      with a working `rebar` on its path.\n      Proving command (run against a throwaway name, then clean up):\n      `make worktree name=__wt_probe && test -x ../__wt_probe/.venv/bin/rebar && ( cd ../__wt_probe && git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD | grep -qx __wt_probe ) && echo CREATE-OK`\n      Cleanup: `git worktree remove --force ../__wt_probe && git branch -D __wt_probe`\n- [ ] The target is listed by `make help` (has a `## ` description) and is in `.PHONY`.\n      Proving command: `make help | grep -q 'worktree' && grep -q '^\\.PHONY:.*worktree' Makefile && echo HELP-OK`\n- [ ] `docs/local-dev-env.md` references `make worktree name=` as the one-command setup.\n      Proving command: `grep -q 'make worktree' docs/local-dev-env.md && echo DOC-OK`\n- [ ] Existing gates stay green (Makefile is not Python, but the repo's checks must pass).\n      Proving command: `make lint && make typecheck` both exit 0.","id":"11c3-d318-e535-480c","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Add 'make worktree name=<branch>' one-command worktree+venv bootstrap target"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784155850605168001,"uuid":"d35769df-b4b7-45e5-8e90-7822138ce4dc"}